      "content": "The timeline is pretty aggressive. We're looking at turning off the agentic services by the end of next month to save on infra costs. Once the middleware is gone, the codebase will mostly just be stateless functions. I haven't seen a rollback plan in the PR because the goal is a permanent migration away from the agent-driven model. Does anything in the current module look like it would break if we just pulled the plug?",
